{{See|gît}}
==English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /gɪt/
===Etymology ===
from Middle English ''get'' 'offspring' (especially 'illegitimate offspring')

====Noun====
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''git'''
#(''British slang'') A contemptible person.
#:*Sid is a right '''git'''.
#(''British slang'') A [[stupid]] or [[unpleasant]] person.
#:*Jacko is a '''git'''.

====Usage notes====
Generally used affectionately. 'Get' can also be used, with a subtle change of meaning. 'You cheeky get!' is slightly less harsh than 'You cheeky git!'. 

===Verb===
[[Category:English verbs]]
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|git||t}}
#(''Appalachia & Southern US'') To [[get]]

